You cannot define a credible SLA that guarantees developer happiness stays above 95% because happiness is subjective and not fully controlled by a rubber duck. At most, you can define a non-binding team objective: track daily self-reported happiness, review trends, and assign any action items to human managers or team leads. The duck can be part of a morale ritual, but enforcement penalties for the duck are not meaningful governance.
